pullRequest.title: Plagiarism check for modeling exercises
pullRequest.bodyText:
Checklist

 I tested all changes and all related features with different users (student, tutor, instructor, admin) on the test server https://artemistest.ase.in.tum.de.
 Server: I added multiple integration tests (Spring) related to the features
 Server: I added @PreAuthorize and check the course groups for all new REST Calls (security)
 Server: I implemented the changes with a good performance and prevented too many database calls
 Server: I documented the Java code using JavaDoc style.

Motivation and Context
Instructors should be able to check plagiarism for modeling exercises
Description

Add new endpoint that reports the results in the JSON response (this will be enhanced in the future)
Use the existing similarity checks as part of Compass for class and activity diagrams
Add support for similarity checks of UML communication diagrams
Additional diagram types (use case, deployment, component) will be implemented in a follow up PR.

Steps for Testing

Create a modeling exercises
Submit 2 identical models from different students
Navigate to the modeling exercise --> view --> Check plagiarism
Look into the Chrome network tab and check that the response includes a similarity of 1.0

commit.message:
initial implementation of the REST endpoint

implement parsing of communication diagrams in Compass
client implementation of the button
add tests and improve similarity calculation for communication diagrams
Merge branch 'develop' of https://github.com/ls1intum/Artemis into feature/plagiarism-check-modeling
improve consistency between text and modeling plagiarism checks
improve logs and use minimum similarity of 80% in text exercises
improve UML data model in compass
fix test after changing distance to similiarity
